### Spring Boot CRUD Application - API Tests
### Use the REST Client extension in VSCode to run these tests
### Install: humao.rest-client

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/users

### 1. Create a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "phone": "1234567890",
  "address": "123 Main Street, New York, NY"
}

### 2. Create another user
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Smith",
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "phone": "0987654321",
  "address": "456 Oak Avenue, Los Angeles, CA"
}

### 3. Get all users
GET {{baseUrl}}

### 4. Get user by ID (change ID as needed)
GET {{baseUrl}}/1

### 5. Get user by email
GET {{baseUrl}}/email/john.doe@example.com

### 6. Update user (change ID as needed)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe Updated",
  "email": "john.updated@example.com",
  "phone": "5555555555",
  "address": "789 Pine Road, Chicago, IL"
}

### 7. Delete user (change ID as needed)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/1

### 8. Try to get deleted user (should return 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/1

### 9. Create user with duplicate email (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Duplicate User",
  "email": "jane.smith@example.com",
  "phone": "1111111111",
  "address": "999 Test Street"
}

### 10. H2 Database Console
### Open in browser: http://localhost:8080/h2-console
### JDBC URL: jdbc:h2:mem:testdb
### Username: sa
### Password: (leave empty)